children.name: butterfly stroke
children.definition: / the butterflya way of swimming on your front by kicking with your legs while raising your arms together out of the water and then bringing them down in front of you : bơi bướm
examples: Her only weak stroke was the butterfly, and this stood in the way of her improving in the IM events.

children.name: doggy paddle
children.definition: / dog paddleUS  a simple way of swimming by moving your legs and arms up and down :bơi chó
examples: He wasn't such a great swimmer, about his only move was the doggy-paddle.

children.name: breaststroke
children.definition: a way of swimming in which the arms make a circular movement in front of the body while the knees are brought up towards the body and then kicked out and back : kiểu bơi ếch
examples: I can onlydobreaststroke.

children.name: backstroke
children.definition: a way of swimming on your back by moving first one arm then the other backwards while kicking your feet : bơi ngửa
examples: Can youdobackstroke?

children.name: the crawl
children.definition: crawl a swimming stroke involving alternate overarm movements and rapid kicks of the legs: bơi trườn
examples: the crawl
she could do the crawl and so many other strokes

children.name: stroke
children.definition: a)one of a set of movements in swimming or rowing in which you move your arms or the oar forward and then back :
examples: She swam with strong steady strokes.
b)a style of swimming or rowing : kiểu bơi
the breast stroke

children.name: diver
children.definition: a person who who dives as a sport or who works or searches for things under water using special breathing equipment thợ lặn
examples: He was a diver on a North Sea oil rig.
pearl divera person who swims deep down into the sea to find shells containing pearls : thợ lặn tìm ngọc trai
scuba diver

skin diver

children.name: swimmer
children.definition: a)sb who swims well, often as a competitor : vận động viên bơi lội, kình ngư
examples: good/strong swimmer
Peter’s a very strong swimmer.
b) sb who is swimming : người bơi

children.name: springboard
children.definition: a board that can bend which helps you to jump higher when jumping or diving into a swimming pool or when doing gymnastics : ván nhún

children.name: flipper
children.definition: a large flat rubber shoe that you wear to help you swim faster : chân vịt
examples: Customers can also win a pair of Turkey feet - like rubber flippers.

children.name: waterwings
children.definition: US armbandUK two bags filled with air that you fasten on your arms when you are learning to swim : phao tập bơi
examples: Home I went seeing as I didn't have my waterwings with me.

children.name: snorkel
children.definition: a tube that you hold in your mouth to help you breatheif you are swimming with your face under water : ống thở (của người lặn)

children.name: diving board
children.definition: a board above the edge of a swimming pool which people dive from : ván nhún

children.name: freestyle
children.definition: a swimming race in which swimmers can use any style they choose, usually crawl : thi bơi tự do
examples: the 100m freestyle
He won the 400 metres freestyle.

children.name: diving
children.definition: the sport of swimming under water using special equipment to help you breathe : môn lặn
examples: go diving

scuba diving[U]the sport of swimming under water with special breathing equipment : nặn với bình khí nén

scuba-diving courses
skin diving[U] the sport of swimming under water with only limited breathing equipment and without a special suit : môn lặn trần
diving[U] B1 the sport or activity of diving into water from a diving board : môn nhảy

children.name: aquaerobics
children.definition: aquarobics aerobic exercises performed in water : thể dục nhịp điệu dưới nước

children.name: snorkelling

examples: go snorkelling

children.name: swimming
children.definition: the sport of moving yourself through water using your arms and legs : bơi

go swimming

synchronized swimminga sport in which a group of people make smooth attractive movements like dancing in the water at the same time bơi theo nhạc

children.name: skinny-dipping
children.definition: informalswimming with no clothes on :

children.name: water park
children.definition: mainly US a large area containing several different pools with equipment and activities for swimmers, which visitors pay to use : công viên nước

children.name: lane
children.definition: a special strip of a swimming pool that is used to keep competitors separate : làn bơi

children.name: pool
children.definition: a hole or container that has been specially made and filled with water so that people can swim or play in it:hồ bơi

children.name: plunge
children.definition: to jump into a river, lake etc quickly, making a lot of noise: đâm sầm

children.name: out of your depth

children.name: tread water
children.definition: to float vertically in the water by moving the legs and the arms up and down : đứng nước
examples: they were at the deep end of the pool and trod water to keep afloat

children.name: dive
children.definition: B1to jump into deep water with your head and arms going in first : nhảy
examples: Roger was standing at the edge of the pool ready to dive.
dive into/off etc

children.name: wetsuit
children.definition: aclose-fitting rubber garment typically covering the entire body, worn for warmth in water sports or diving: đồ lặn

children.name: length
children.definition: the distance from one end of a swimming pool to the other
examples: She swims forty lengths a day.

children.name: width
children.definition: the distance across a swimming pool from one side to the other
examples: I managed to swim 2 widths underwater.

children.name: lap
children.definition: USa single journey from one end of a swimming pool to another : vòng bơi
examples: do/swim a lap
